WEBVTT

00:00:01.870 --> 00:00:06.469
The theme for this month is, in whom do you trust?

00:00:06.469 --> 00:00:08.070
Do you trust me?

00:00:08.070 --> 00:00:09.470
I hope so.

00:00:09.470 --> 00:00:11.470
All of us want to be trusted.

00:00:11.470 --> 00:00:15.869
A trust is a basic element of everyday life.

00:00:15.869 --> 00:00:18.870
To trust others is a normal reaction.

00:00:18.870 --> 00:00:22.469
Many of us have traveled on the train or bus.

00:00:22.469 --> 00:00:27.870
Did we worry whether the conductor or driver would bring a safely to our destination?

00:00:27.870 --> 00:00:30.070
Normally, we do not worry.

00:00:30.070 --> 00:00:35.070
We trust an airplane captain to take us safely to our destination.

00:00:35.070 --> 00:00:38.070
We trust that when we enter an elevator,

00:00:38.070 --> 00:00:41.070
that it will not crash at the bottom of the shaft,

00:00:41.070 --> 00:00:44.070
but safely take us to the desired floor.

00:00:44.070 --> 00:00:49.070
When we marry, we trust that our partner will remain faithful.

00:00:49.070 --> 00:00:53.070
In many situations in life, we need trust.

00:00:53.070 --> 00:00:55.070
What is trust?

00:00:55.070 --> 00:00:59.070
Trust is the firm belief in the reliability, truth,

00:00:59.070 --> 00:01:03.070
or ability of someone or something.

00:01:03.070 --> 00:01:07.069
Webster's dictionary says that it is confidence,

00:01:07.069 --> 00:01:11.069
a reliance or resting of the mind on the integrity,

00:01:11.069 --> 00:01:14.069
veracity, justice, friendship,

00:01:14.069 --> 00:01:18.069
or other sound principle of another person.

00:01:18.069 --> 00:01:24.069
Trust is related to confidence, belief, faith, and assurance.

00:01:25.069 --> 00:01:29.069
Experiments conducted by Professor Dr. Mikhail Kosfeld,

00:01:29.069 --> 00:01:33.069
a professor at a university in Frankfurt, Germany,

00:01:33.069 --> 00:01:41.069
led him to the conclusion that trust is a biologically-based part of human nature.

00:01:41.069 --> 00:01:46.069
Kosfeld discovered that when there's interaction between two people,

00:01:46.069 --> 00:01:51.069
the human brain releases a hormone that stimulates trust.

00:01:52.069 --> 00:01:59.069
It is, in fact, one of the distinguishing features of the human species, Kosfeld states.

00:01:59.069 --> 00:02:04.069
In everyday life, how discouraged some are if they are not trusted.

00:02:04.069 --> 00:02:07.069
The phrase, don't you trust me?

00:02:07.069 --> 00:02:12.069
Is frequently heard with an undertone of sadness or complaint?

00:02:12.069 --> 00:02:17.069
Sometimes children or teenagers ask their parents, don't you trust me?

00:02:17.069 --> 00:02:20.069
When the parents place some restrictions on them,

00:02:20.069 --> 00:02:24.069
perhaps in connection with leisure time activities.

00:02:24.069 --> 00:02:27.069
Parents do that because they love you young ones

00:02:27.069 --> 00:02:32.069
and want to prevent any spiritual or physical harm before you.

00:02:32.069 --> 00:02:38.069
If you cooperate, you will see that parents will gradually trust you ever more

00:02:38.069 --> 00:02:42.069
and grant you more liberty to you.

00:02:42.069 --> 00:02:46.069
You can prove to them that you are trustworthy.

00:02:46.069 --> 00:02:49.069
In the world, many people are not trustworthy.

00:02:49.069 --> 00:02:52.069
Since we are living in the time of the end,

00:02:52.069 --> 00:02:56.069
and the demons are desperate and have influenced many people,

00:02:56.069 --> 00:03:02.069
we have to admit that trusting in everybody is not wise.

00:03:02.069 --> 00:03:05.069
Many trusted in religion and were disappointed.

00:03:05.069 --> 00:03:11.069
Others trusted in governments or the United Nations, but they were disappointed.

00:03:11.069 --> 00:03:14.069
They trusted political leaders that made all kinds of promises,

00:03:14.069 --> 00:03:17.069
but did not keep all of them.

00:03:17.069 --> 00:03:22.069
Some politicians even were exposed as being liars.

00:03:22.069 --> 00:03:24.069
Proverbs 14, 15 says,

00:03:24.069 --> 00:03:27.069
the naive person believes every word,

00:03:27.069 --> 00:03:31.069
but the shrewd one ponders each step.

00:03:31.069 --> 00:03:36.069
If somebody, even in the truth, promises as big monetary returns

00:03:36.069 --> 00:03:39.069
if we give him money for his plant investment,

00:03:39.069 --> 00:03:43.069
we need to be careful and not believe every word.

00:03:43.069 --> 00:03:48.069
Some that spent their money were in for a disappointment when they learned

00:03:48.069 --> 00:03:51.069
that everything was lost.

00:03:51.069 --> 00:03:58.069
We also should not trust everything we read in newspapers or see on television.

00:03:58.069 --> 00:04:01.069
There's another thing we should not trust in.

00:04:01.069 --> 00:04:03.069
Riches.

00:04:03.069 --> 00:04:07.069
Psalm 496 speaks about those who are trusting in their wealth

00:04:07.069 --> 00:04:11.069
and who boast about their great riches.

00:04:11.069 --> 00:04:15.069
Trusting in riches often leads to disappointment.

00:04:15.069 --> 00:04:22.069
The one trusting in his riches will fall, says Proverbs 11, 28.

00:04:22.069 --> 00:04:27.069
It is not wrong to be rich, just do not trust in riches.

00:04:27.069 --> 00:04:31.069
Riches are a risk factor.

00:04:31.069 --> 00:04:34.069
Many people today are dishonest and cheat.

00:04:34.069 --> 00:04:38.069
Some business owners have installed cameras at the workplace

00:04:38.069 --> 00:04:43.069
since they do not trust their employees to put in a full day of work.

00:04:43.069 --> 00:04:48.069
They know that some would play video games during work hours.

00:04:48.069 --> 00:04:53.069
But Jehovah created us with the inclination to trust.

00:04:53.069 --> 00:04:57.069
We can especially trust our spiritual brothers.

00:04:57.069 --> 00:05:00.069
True, once in a while such trust is misplaced,

00:05:00.069 --> 00:05:07.069
a few commit serious sins and have to be disfellowshipped, but that is rare.

00:05:07.069 --> 00:05:12.069
Jehovah himself is the best example of trusting in others.

00:05:12.069 --> 00:05:18.069
He trusted the logos to faithfully cooperate with him as the master worker

00:05:18.069 --> 00:05:25.069
in creating the universe, the earth, and all the living things on earth, including mankind.

00:05:25.069 --> 00:05:28.069
What tremendous trust Jehovah showed in Jesus

00:05:28.069 --> 00:05:31.069
when he sent him to the earth.

00:05:31.069 --> 00:05:36.069
Jehovah trusted that Jesus would remain faithful and redeem mankind

00:05:36.069 --> 00:05:42.069
so that his will and purpose with mankind and the earth could be accomplished.

00:05:42.069 --> 00:05:47.069
Jehovah trusted him so much that he arranged for prophecies to be written

00:05:47.069 --> 00:05:50.069
that foretold that he would die faithfully.

00:05:50.069 --> 00:05:54.069
This trust on the part of Jehovah was not a risk.

00:05:54.069 --> 00:06:01.069
It was based on the collaboration between the two for eons of time.

00:06:01.069 --> 00:06:04.069
Think of the prophecy in Psalm 1610,

00:06:04.069 --> 00:06:09.069
for you will not leave me in the grave.

00:06:09.069 --> 00:06:11.069
Jesus had free will.

00:06:11.069 --> 00:06:15.069
This means that theoretically he could have sinned.

00:06:15.069 --> 00:06:23.069
If he could not have sinned, Satan would probably not have tried three times to tempt Jesus to sin.

00:06:23.069 --> 00:06:29.069
If Jesus could not have sinned, why would he be so heavily distressed in the Garden of Gethsemane

00:06:29.069 --> 00:06:31.069
that he was sweating blood?

00:06:31.069 --> 00:06:39.069
Why send an angel to comfort and strengthen him if he could not sin or fail anyway?

00:06:39.069 --> 00:06:40.069
No question.

00:06:40.069 --> 00:06:47.069
Jesus felt the unfathomable load on his shoulders to remain faithful

00:06:47.069 --> 00:06:51.069
since not only the salvation of mankind depended on him,

00:06:51.069 --> 00:06:55.069
but also the vindication of Jehovah's sovereignty.

00:06:55.069 --> 00:06:58.069
He did not want to disappoint Jehovah.

00:06:58.069 --> 00:07:04.069
Jesus used his own free will and was determined to stay loyal.

00:07:04.069 --> 00:07:08.069
How glad we are that he did.

00:07:08.069 --> 00:07:13.069
On the other hand, Jesus also trusted Jehovah completely.

00:07:13.069 --> 00:07:19.069
He trusted Jehovah that he would resurrect him if he would die faithfully.

00:07:19.069 --> 00:07:23.069
Actually, Jesus was publicly known to trust in Jehovah.

00:07:23.069 --> 00:07:28.069
People that passed by when he was on the torture stake were saying,

00:07:28.069 --> 00:07:34.069
he has put his trust in God, let him now rescue him if he wants him.

00:07:34.069 --> 00:07:37.069
For he said, I am God's son.

00:07:37.069 --> 00:07:40.069
Another example of trust was Abraham.

00:07:40.069 --> 00:07:46.069
When God told him to kill his beloved son Isaac, Abraham was willing to do so.

00:07:46.069 --> 00:07:50.069
He trusted that Jehovah could resurrect him.

00:07:50.069 --> 00:07:58.069
Hebrews 11, 19 says, he reasoned that God was able to raise him up even from the dead.

00:07:58.069 --> 00:08:02.069
And he did receive him from there in an illustrative way.

00:08:02.069 --> 00:08:09.069
1 Corinthians 137 says, that love believes all things.

00:08:09.069 --> 00:08:13.069
Love trust that prophecies will come true.

00:08:13.069 --> 00:08:17.069
It also believes what our brothers tell us.

00:08:17.069 --> 00:08:24.069
It also helps to grant others the benefit of the doubt if a matter could be interpreted in different ways.

00:08:24.069 --> 00:08:28.069
Yes, trusting others is an expression of love.

00:08:28.069 --> 00:08:33.070
If you love somebody, you only assume and think the best of him.

00:08:33.070 --> 00:08:38.450
Another example of trust in Jehovah was Moses.

00:08:38.450 --> 00:08:43.450
He led the nation of Israel out of Egypt into the desert.

00:08:43.450 --> 00:08:46.450
A nation of upwards of three million people.

00:08:46.450 --> 00:08:50.450
And they had flocks of cattle and sheep with them.

00:08:50.450 --> 00:08:57.450
When he left Egypt, did he know how to provide these great crowds with water in the desert?

00:08:57.450 --> 00:09:04.450
Did he know what they would be eating after the initial foodstuffs that they took out of Egypt would run out?

00:09:04.450 --> 00:09:09.450
Did he know in advance that Jehovah would miraculously provide the manor?

00:09:10.450 --> 00:09:12.450
It doesn't seem so.

00:09:12.450 --> 00:09:16.450
But he trusted that Jehovah would take care of the people.

00:09:16.450 --> 00:09:22.860
The three friends of Daniel were another fine example of trust.

00:09:22.860 --> 00:09:28.860
They did not bow and worship in front of an idol that King Nebuchadnezzar had set up.

00:09:28.860 --> 00:09:34.860
They were told they would be thrown into a fiery furnace if they disobeyed.

00:09:35.860 --> 00:09:39.860
They remained firm and were protected by an angel,

00:09:39.860 --> 00:09:42.860
so the fire did not do any harm to them.

00:09:42.860 --> 00:09:46.860
After that, Nebuchadnezzar then declared,

00:09:46.860 --> 00:09:51.860
praised me the God of Shadrach, Mishak and Abednego,

00:09:51.860 --> 00:09:54.860
who sent his angel and rescued his servants.

00:09:54.860 --> 00:09:58.860
They trusted in him and went against the command of the King

00:09:58.860 --> 00:10:03.860
and were willing to die rather than serve or worship any God except their own God.

